Design a task system where users can quickly add tasks from a queue card and progressively structure work into deep nested trees, while enforcing valid sequential dependencies.

Core UX
On first view, user sees the Task Queue with a primary queue card.
The queue card contains a prominent + button.
Clicking + opens an inline popover (anchored to the button) containing:
Task title
Priority
Estimated minutes
Notes
Reference link
Add Task action
Submitting creates a new task card in the queue.
Task Card Actions
Each created task card supports:

Add Sub-task
Add Sequential Task Right After
Hierarchy Rules
Sub-task nesting is unlimited depth.
Any sub-task can itself create:
more sub-tasks
sequential tasks
Sequential Rules
Sequential tasks are allowed only for same-level siblings under the same parent.
“Add sequential task right after it” behavior:
creates a new sibling directly after the current task
auto-sets dependsOn = currentTaskId
Guardrails are strict:
block dependency cycles
block dependencies outside sibling scope
do not auto-correct invalid dependencies
show clear inline validation when blocked
Parent Completion Behavior
Parent task auto-completes only when all descendants (not just direct children) are complete.
Default Tree Presentation
Nested branches are collapsed by default.
Show progress summary on collapsed parents (example: 2/5 complete).
User can expand/collapse branches.
Required Interaction/State Behavior
Preserve stable sibling ordering and ensure sequential insertion keeps relative order.
Sequentially locked tasks are visually indicated and non-actionable until dependency completes.
On dependency completion, unlock state updates immediately.
Notes and reference links are editable and persisted per task.
Reference links open in a new tab.
Acceptance Criteria
User can create unlimited-depth nested tasks.
User can create sequential sibling tasks at any depth.
Invalid dependencies cannot be saved (cross-scope or cycles).
Parent completion reflects all descendant states.
Collapsed-by-default tree renders accurate progress counts.
Inline popover creation flow is keyboard accessible and fast for repeated entry.
